      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>ginger</strong> with the <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>ground coriander</strong>, <strong>ground</strong> <strong>turmeric</strong>,<strong> garam masala </strong>and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>natural yoghurt </strong>(you’ll use the rest later!)<strong> </strong>in a medium bowl</p><p>Add the juice of 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]<strong> </span>lemon </strong>and season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>tandoori marinade</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>basa fillets</strong> to the <strong>tandoori marinade</strong> and mix well until they're completely coated – this is your <strong>tandoori basa</strong></p>",
